# 20. 最初からあった歌

Mafuyu: .....
Miku: Mafuyu, you've come.
Mafuyu: Right.
Miku: What are you doing?
Mafuyu: I'm writing a song.
Miku: I see. You were writing a song last time you were here as well.
Miku: You must enjoy it.
Mafuyu: Enjoy...?
Mafuyu: I don't really understand what enjoying something feels like.
Miku: I see...
Mafuyu: .....
Miku: (She's stopped speaking again.)
Miku: (She'll probably be working on her songs all day again.)
Miku: (That's all she's been doing ever since she first came here.)
Miku: (And yet...she has yet to find her true feelings.)
Miku: (I wonder if there is anything I can do to help her find them.)
Mafuyu: .....
Miku: .....
Miku: (I just can't seem to think of any good ideas...)
Miku: (What should I do?)
Miku: (I get the feeling just sitting here worrying about it isn't going to help me come up with something.)
Miku: Oh, I know.
Miku: If I take a look around this SEKAI, maybe I'll think of something.
Miku: Oh...
Miku: (It looks like I'm back where I started.)
Miku: (Now what? I wasn't able to think of anything...)
Mafuyu: .....
Miku: (There's so many more pages than before.)
Miku: (It looks like she's been writing this entire time.)
Miku: (What can I possibly do to help her?)
Miku: ♪————
Mafuyu: Miku, that song...
Miku: Mafuyu?
Mafuyu: How do you know that song?
Miku: This song...
Miku: I've known this song...from the beginning.
Mafuyu: From the beginning?
Miku: Yes. Since this SEKAI was created. That's why I sing it.
Mafuyu: I see. So you've always known it...
Miku: Right.
Mafuyu: .....
Miku: (She's gone back to writing her songs...)
Miku: (Still, I am a little relieved that she still pays some attention to things other than the songs she is writing.)
Miku: (I wonder if this song is important to her somehow.)
